'''Ratshit''' 

To look/feel [[depression|depressed]], unwell, exhausted etc, not to be mistaken for emotional hardship, it is based on [[physical exhaustion]].

It is [[Australian]] [[slang]] for "you look really depressed", eg: ''You look like ratshit mate'', or ''I feel like ratshit mate''. Used only when someone looks/feels truly terrible, can be offensive if used in other cultures or said to someone without the ability to laugh at themselves. It has also been used to describe something aweful: ''that exam was ratshit''. Pronounced (rasssh it) Also refer 'maggeted'.